Three vehicles were stoned and another burned beyond repair by an unidentified group of protesters on the N2 this afternoon (06/06/17). Picture: Eugene Coetzee Police are urging motorists to avoid Ikamvelihle in Motherwell. According to police spokesman captain Andre Beetge, protest action is flaring up in the area &#8211; a continuation from this afternoon&#8217;s riots. &#8220;Residents and motorists are advise to use extreme caution when entering this area, particularly the Addo Road and M17. Protesters are pelting stones at passing motorists and police,&#8221; he said. Beetge added that the scene was being monitored and police were attempting to calm the situation. This is a developing story. Share on Facebook Share Share on Twitter Tweet Share on Google Plus Share